alaDyingGaspChassisId.name: alaDyingGaspChassisId
alaDyingGaspChassisId.description: This object specifies the chassis id of the chassis whose NI is going down.

alaDyingGaspPowerSupplyType.name: alaDyingGaspPowerSupplyType
alaDyingGaspPowerSupplyType.description: This object specifies the type of the power supply.

alaDyingGaspTime.name: alaDyingGaspTime
alaDyingGaspTime.description: This object specifies the time of power failure.

esmConfTable.name: esmConfTable
esmConfTable.description: A list of ESM Physical Port instances.

esmPortSlot.name: esmPortSlot
esmPortSlot.description: The physical Slot number for this Ethernet Port. Slot number has been added to be used by the private Trap.

esmPortIF.name: esmPortIF
esmPortIF.description: The on-board interface number for this Ethernet Port. Port Number has been added to be used by the private Trap.

esmPortAutoSpeed.name: esmPortAutoSpeed
esmPortAutoSpeed.description: The automatically detected port line speed of this ESM port.

esmPortAutoDuplexMode.name: esmPortAutoDuplexMode
esmPortAutoDuplexMode.description: The automatically detected port duplex mode of this ESM port. Note: GigaEthernet supports only Full duplex mode. Default value for 10/100 = Half duplex mode.

esmPortCfgSpeed.name: esmPortCfgSpeed
esmPortCfgSpeed.description: The configured port line speed of this ESM port.

esmPortCfgDuplexMode.name: esmPortCfgDuplexMode
esmPortCfgDuplexMode.description: The configured port duplex mode of this ESM port. Note: GigaEthernet support only full-duplex.

esmPortAdminStatus.name: esmPortAdminStatus
esmPortAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed. When a managed system initializes, all interfaces start with ifAdminStatus in the down(2) state. As a result of either explicit management action or per configuration information retained by the managed system, ifAdminStatus is then changed to either the up(1) or testing(3) states (or remains in the down(2) state).

esmPortLinkUpDownTrapEnable.name: esmPortLinkUpDownTrapEnable
esmPortLinkUpDownTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether linkUp/linkDown traps should be generated for this interface. By default, this object should have the value enable(1) for interfaces which do not operate on 'top' of any other interface (as defined in the ifStackTable), and disable(2) otherwise.

esmPortCfgMaxFrameSize.name: esmPortCfgMaxFrameSize
esmPortCfgMaxFrameSize.description: Configure the value of the maximum frame size allow. For 10Mbps the range is upto 1518 bytes. For ports with speed > 10Mbps the value can extend upto 9216 bytes.

esmPortAlias.name: esmPortAlias
esmPortAlias.description: This object is an 'alias' name for the interface as specified by a network manager, and provides a non-volatile 'handle' for the interface. On the first instantiation of an interface, the value of ifAlias associated with that interface is the zero-length string. As and when a value is written into an instance of ifAlias through a network management set operation, then the agent must retain the supplied value in the ifAlias instance associated with the same interface for as long as that interface remains instantiated, including across all re- initializations/reboots of the network management system, including those which result in a change of the interface's ifIndex value. An example of the value which a network manager might store in this object for a WAN interface is the (Telco's) circuit number/identifier of the interface. Some agents may support write-access only for interfaces having particular values of ifType. An agent which supports write access to this object is required to keep the value in non-volatile storage, but it may limit the length of new values depending on how much storage is already occupied by the current values for other interfaces.

esmPortCfgPause.name: esmPortCfgPause
esmPortCfgPause.description: This object is used to configure the default administrative PAUSE mode for this interface. This object represents the administratively-configured PAUSE mode for this interface. If auto-negotiation is not enabled or is not implemented for the active MAU attached to this interface, the value of this object determines the operational PAUSE mode of the interface whenever it is operating in full-duplex mode. In this case, a set to this object will force the interface into the specified mode. If auto-negotiation is implemented and enabled for the MAU attached to this interface, the PAUSE mode for this interface is determined by auto-negotiation, and the value of this object denotes the mode to which the interface will automatically revert if/when auto-negotiation is later disabled. For more information on what pause values will be autonegotiated based on settings on this object, please refer to the truth table in the users manual. Note that the value of this object is ignored when the interface is not operating in full-duplex mode.

esmPortCfgAutoNegotiation.name: esmPortCfgAutoNegotiation
esmPortCfgAutoNegotiation.description: Allow the user to enable or disable the port auto negotiation.

esmPortCfgCrossover.name: esmPortCfgCrossover
esmPortCfgCrossover.description: Allow the user to configure port crossover. This object is applicable only to copper ports. For fiber ports notapplicable is returned as a status.

esmPortCfgHybridActiveType.name: esmPortCfgHybridActiveType
esmPortCfgHybridActiveType.description: This object is only applicable to hybrid ports . It indicates configured active media type.(the operational media type may be different if esmPortCfgHybridMode is configured to be preferredFiber or preferredCopper) For non hybrid ports notapplicable is returned as a status.

esmPortCfgHybridMode.name: esmPortCfgHybridMode
esmPortCfgHybridMode.description: This object is only applicable to hybrid ports. This allows the user the user to configure the media type with which the port should come up. The user can configure the port to come as copper only or fiber only or either fiber/copper (with preference to one of them).

esmPortOperationalHybridType.name: esmPortOperationalHybridType
esmPortOperationalHybridType.description: This object is only applicable to hybrid ports . It indicates the actual media type that has link up and is or will be passing traffic. If link is not present the object will return none(0) value.

esmPortBcastRateLimitEnable.name: esmPortBcastRateLimitEnable
esmPortBcastRateLimitEnable.description: Enable/disable per port broadcast traffic rate limit. When 'enable' value from esmPortBcastRateLimit object will be applicable to the ingressing broadcast traffic if the speed is greater than the limit else the default limit for the speed will be applied. When it is 'disable' no limit is applied to incoming broadcast traffic which is limited by the port speed.

esmPortBcastRateLimitType.name: esmPortBcastRateLimitType
esmPortBcastRateLimitType.description: The unit applicable to the value in esmPortBcastRateLimit object.

esmPortBcastRateLimit.name: esmPortBcastRateLimit
esmPortBcastRateLimit.description: The value of the maximum broadcast traffic that can flow through the port. The actual value depends on the port speed if the configured values is greater than the current port speed.

esmPortMcastRateLimitEnable.name: esmPortMcastRateLimitEnable
esmPortMcastRateLimitEnable.description: Enable/disable per port multicast traffic rate limit. When 'enable' value from esmPortMcastRateLimit object will be applicable to the ingressing multicast traffic if the speed is greater than the limit else the default limit for the speed will be applied. When it is 'disable' no limit is applied to incoming multicast traffic which is limited by the port speed.

esmPortMcastRateLimitType.name: esmPortMcastRateLimitType
esmPortMcastRateLimitType.description: The unit applicable to the value in esmPortMcastRateLimit object.

esmPortMcastRateLimit.name: esmPortMcastRateLimit
esmPortMcastRateLimit.description: The value of the maximum multicast traffic that can flow through the port. The actual value depends on the port speed if the configured values is greater than the current port speed.

esmPortUucastRateLimitEnable.name: esmPortUucastRateLimitEnable
esmPortUucastRateLimitEnable.description: Enable/disable per port unknown unicast traffic rate limit. When 'enable' value from esmPortUucastRateLimit object will be applicable to the ingressing unknown unicast traffic if the speed is greater than the limit else the default limit for the speed will be applied. When it is 'disable' no limit is applied to incoming unknown unicast traffic which is limited by the port speed.

esmPortUucastRateLimitType.name: esmPortUucastRateLimitType
esmPortUucastRateLimitType.description: The unit applicable to the value in esmPortUucastRate object.

esmPortUucastRateLimit.name: esmPortUucastRateLimit
esmPortUucastRateLimit.description: The value of the maximum unknown unicast traffic that can flow through the port. The actual value depends on the port speed if the configured values is greater than the current port speed.

esmPortIngressRateLimitEnable.name: esmPortIngressRateLimitEnable
esmPortIngressRateLimitEnable.description: Enable/disable per port ingress traffic rate limit. When 'enable' value from esmPortIngressRate object will be applicable to the ingressing traffic (BC, MC, UUC) if the speed is greater than the limit else the default limit for the speed will be applied. When it is 'disable' no limit is applied to incoming traffic which is limited by the port speed.

esmPortIngressRateLimit.name: esmPortIngressRateLimit
esmPortIngressRateLimit.description: The value of the maximum ingress traffic that can flow through the port. The actual value depends on the port speed if the configured value is greater than the current port speed.

esmPortIngressRateLimitBurst.name: esmPortIngressRateLimitBurst
esmPortIngressRateLimitBurst.description: The value of ingress traffic burst size in Mbits.

esmPortIsFiberChannelCapable.name: esmPortIsFiberChannelCapable
esmPortIsFiberChannelCapable.description: The port can be configured as Fiber Channel interface (yes) or can not be configured as Fiber Channel interface.

alcetherStatsTable.name: alcetherStatsTable
alcetherStatsTable.description: A list of Ethernet statistics entries.

alcetherStatsEntry.name: alcetherStatsEntry
alcetherStatsEntry.description: A collection of statistics kept for a particular Ethernet interface. As an example, an instance of the etherStatsPkts object might be named alcetherStatsPkts.1

alcetherClearStats.name: alcetherClearStats
alcetherClearStats.description: Used to Clear all Statistics counters. By default, this object contains zero value.

alcetherLastClearStats.name: alcetherLastClearStats
alcetherLastClearStats.description: The value of SysUpTime at the time of all the statistics counters are cleared. By default, this object contains a zero value.

alcetherStatsCRCAlignErrors.name: alcetherStatsCRCAlignErrors
alcetherStatsCRCAlignErrors.description: The total number of packets received that had a length (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) of between 64 and 1518 octets, inclusive, but but had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) with an integral number of octets (FCS Error) or a bad FCS with a non-integral number of octets (Alignment Error).

alcetherStatsRxUndersizePkts.name: alcetherStatsRxUndersizePkts
alcetherStatsRxUndersizePkts.description: The total number of packets received that were less than 64 octets long (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed.

alcetherStatsTxUndersizePkts.name: alcetherStatsTxUndersizePkts
alcetherStatsTxUndersizePkts.description: The total number of packets transmitted that were less than 64 octets long (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed.

alcetherStatsTxOversizePkts.name: alcetherStatsTxOversizePkts
alcetherStatsTxOversizePkts.description: The total number of packets transmitted that were longer than 1518 octets long (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed.

alcetherStatsRxJabbers.name: alcetherStatsRxJabbers
alcetherStatsRxJabbers.description: The total number of packets received that were longer than 1518 octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets), and had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) with an integral number of octets (FCS Error) or a bad FCS with a non-integral number of octets (Alignment Error). Note that this definition of jabber is different than the definition in IEEE-802.3 section 8.2.1.5 (10BASE5) and section 10.3.1.4 (10BASE2). These documents define jabber as the condition where any packet exceeds 20 ms. The allowed range to detect jabber is between 20 ms and 150 ms.

alcetherStatsRxCollisions.name: alcetherStatsRxCollisions
alcetherStatsRxCollisions.description: The best estimate of the total number of collisions on this Ethernet segment (in reception). Only for Ethernet Interfaces. The value returned will depend on the location of the RMON probe. Section 8.2.1.3 (10BASE-5) and section 10.3.1.3 (10BASE-2) of IEEE standard 802.3 states that a station must detect a collision, in the receive mode, if three or more stations are transmitting simultaneously. A repeater port must detect a collision when two or more stations are transmitting simultaneously. Thus a probe placed on a repeater port could record more collisions than a probe connected to a station on the same segment would. Probe location plays a much smaller role when considering 10BASE-T. 14.2.1.4 (10BASE-T) of IEEE standard 802.3 defines a collision as the simultaneous presence of signals on the DO and RD circuits (transmitting and receiving at the same time). A 10BASE-T station can only detect collisions when it is transmitting. Thus probes placed on a station and a repeater, should report the same number of collisions. Note also that an RMON probe inside a repeater should ideally report collisions between the repeater and one or more other hosts (transmit collisions as defined by IEEE 802.3k) plus receiver collisions observed on any coax segments to which the repeater is connected.

alcetherStatsTxCollisions.name: alcetherStatsTxCollisions
alcetherStatsTxCollisions.description: The best estimate of the total number of collisions on this Ethernet segment (in transmition). Only for Ethernet Interfaces. The value returned will depend on the location of the RMON probe. Section 8.2.1.3 (10BASE-5) and section 10.3.1.3 (10BASE-2) of IEEE standard 802.3 states that a station must detect a collision, in the receive mode, if three or more stations are transmitting simultaneously. A repeater port must detect a collision when two or more stations are transmitting simultaneously. Thus a probe placed on a repeater port could record more collisions than a probe connected to a station on the same segment would. Probe location plays a much smaller role when considering 10BASE-T. 14.2.1.4 (10BASE-T) of IEEE standard 802.3 defines a collision as the simultaneous presence of signals on the DO and RD circuits (transmitting and receiving at the same time). A 10BASE-T station can only detect collisions when it is transmitting. Thus probes placed on a station and a repeater, should report the same number of collisions. Note also that an RMON probe inside a repeater should ideally report collisions between the repeater and one or more other hosts (transmit collisions as defined by IEEE 802.3k) plus receiver collisions observed on any coax segments to which the repeater is connected.

alcetherStatsPkts64Octets.name: alcetherStatsPkts64Octets
alcetherStatsPkts64Octets.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were 64 octets in length (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

alcetherStatsPkts65to127Octets.name: alcetherStatsPkts65to127Octets
alcetherStatsPkts65to127Octets.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 65 and 127 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

alcetherStatsPkts128to255Octets.name: alcetherStatsPkts128to255Octets
alcetherStatsPkts128to255Octets.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 128 and 255 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

alcetherStatsPkts256to511Octets.name: alcetherStatsPkts256to511Octets
alcetherStatsPkts256to511Octets.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 256 and 511 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

alcetherStatsPkts512to1023Octets.name: alcetherStatsPkts512to1023Octets
alcetherStatsPkts512to1023Octets.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 512 and 1023 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets).

alcetherStatsPkts1024to1518Octets.name: alcetherStatsPkts1024to1518Octets
alcetherStatsPkts1024to1518Octets.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 1024 and 1518 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). For both Ethernet and GigaEthernet.

gigaEtherStatsPkts1519to4095Octets.name: gigaEtherStatsPkts1519to4095Octets
gigaEtherStatsPkts1519to4095Octets.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 1519 and 4095 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). Only for GigaEthernet interfaces

gigaEtherStatsPkts4096to9215Octets.name: gigaEtherStatsPkts4096to9215Octets
gigaEtherStatsPkts4096to9215Octets.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets) received that were between 4096 and 9215 octets in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS octets). Only for GigaEthernet interfaces

alcetherStatsPkts1519to2047Octets.name: alcetherStatsPkts1519to2047Octets
alcetherStatsPkts1519to2047Octets.description: The total number of frames(including error packets) received that were between 1519 and 2047 bytes in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS bytes).

alcetherStatsPkts2048to4095Octets.name: alcetherStatsPkts2048to4095Octets
alcetherStatsPkts2048to4095Octets.description: The total number of frames(including error packets) received that were between 2048 and 4095 bytes in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS bytes).

alcetherStatsPkts4096Octets.name: alcetherStatsPkts4096Octets
alcetherStatsPkts4096Octets.description: The total number of frames(including error packets) received that were greater than or equal to 4096 bytes in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS bytes).

alcetherStatsRxGiantPkts.name: alcetherStatsRxGiantPkts
alcetherStatsRxGiantPkts.description: The total number of frames that are greater than the specified Max length value, with a valid CRC, dropped because too long.

alcetherStatsRxDribbleNibblePkts.name: alcetherStatsRxDribbleNibblePkts
alcetherStatsRxDribbleNibblePkts.description: The total number of frames for which a dribble nibble has been received and CRC is correct.

alcetherStatsRxLongEventPkts.name: alcetherStatsRxLongEventPkts
alcetherStatsRxLongEventPkts.description: The total number of frames for which the Carrier sense exceeds 50000 bit times for 10 Mbits/sec or 80000 bit times for 100 Mbits/sec.

alcetherStatsRxVlanTagPkts.name: alcetherStatsRxVlanTagPkts
alcetherStatsRxVlanTagPkts.description: The total number of frames for which Type/Length field contains the VLAN protocol identifier (0x8100).

alcetherStatsRxControlPkts.name: alcetherStatsRxControlPkts
alcetherStatsRxControlPkts.description: The total number of frames that were recognized as control frames.

alcetherStatsRxLenChkErrPkts.name: alcetherStatsRxLenChkErrPkts
alcetherStatsRxLenChkErrPkts.description: The total number of frames for which the frame length field value in the Type/Length field does not match the actual data bytes length and is NOT a type field.

alcetherStatsRxCodeErrPkts.name: alcetherStatsRxCodeErrPkts
alcetherStatsRxCodeErrPkts.description: The total number of frames for which one or more nibbles were signaled as errors during reception of the frame.

alcetherStatsRxDvEventPkts.name: alcetherStatsRxDvEventPkts
alcetherStatsRxDvEventPkts.description: The total number of frames for which a RX_DV event (packet not too long enough to be valid packet) has been seen before the correct frame.

alcetherStatsRxPrevPktDropped.name: alcetherStatsRxPrevPktDropped
alcetherStatsRxPrevPktDropped.description: The total number of frames for which a packet has been dropped (because of too small IFG) before the correct frame.

alcetherStatsTx64Octets.name: alcetherStatsTx64Octets
alcetherStatsTx64Octets.description: The total number of transmitted frames of 64 bytes.

alcetherStatsTx65to127Octets.name: alcetherStatsTx65to127Octets
alcetherStatsTx65to127Octets.description: The total number of transmitted frames that were between 65 and 127 bytes in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS bytes).

alcetherStatsTx128to255Octets.name: alcetherStatsTx128to255Octets
alcetherStatsTx128to255Octets.description: The total number of transmitted frames that were between 128 and 255 bytes in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS bytes).

alcetherStatsTx256to511Octets.name: alcetherStatsTx256to511Octets
alcetherStatsTx256to511Octets.description: The total number of transmitted frames that were between 256 and 511 bytes in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS bytes).

alcetherStatsTx512to1023Octets.name: alcetherStatsTx512to1023Octets
alcetherStatsTx512to1023Octets.description: The total number of transmitted frames that were between 512 and 1023 bytes in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS bytes).

alcetherStatsTx1024to1518Octets.name: alcetherStatsTx1024to1518Octets
alcetherStatsTx1024to1518Octets.description: The total number of transmitted frames that were between 1024 and 1518 bytes in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS bytes).

alcetherStatsTx1519to2047Octets.name: alcetherStatsTx1519to2047Octets
alcetherStatsTx1519to2047Octets.description: The total number of transmitted frames that were between 1519 and 2047 bytes in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS bytes).

alcetherStatsTx2048to4095Octets.name: alcetherStatsTx2048to4095Octets
alcetherStatsTx2048to4095Octets.description: The total number of transmitted frames that were between 2048 and 4095 bytes in length inclusive (excluding framing bits but including FCS bytes).

alcetherStatsTx4096Octets.name: alcetherStatsTx4096Octets
alcetherStatsTx4096Octets.description: The total number of transmitted frames that were greater than or equal to 4096 bytes in length and less than Max frame length (excluding framing bits but including FCS bytes).

alcetherStatsTxRetryCount.name: alcetherStatsTxRetryCount
alcetherStatsTxRetryCount.description: The total number of collisions that the frames faced during transmission attempts.

alcetherStatsTxVlanTagPkts.name: alcetherStatsTxVlanTagPkts
alcetherStatsTxVlanTagPkts.description: The total number of transmitted frames for which Type/Length field contains the VLAN protocol identifier (0x8100).

alcetherStatsTxControlPkts.name: alcetherStatsTxControlPkts
alcetherStatsTxControlPkts.description: The total number of transmitted frames that were recognised as control frames.

alcetherStatsTxLatePkts.name: alcetherStatsTxLatePkts
alcetherStatsTxLatePkts.description: The total number of late collisions that occured beyond the collision window.

alcetherStatsTxTotalBytesOnWire.name: alcetherStatsTxTotalBytesOnWire
alcetherStatsTxTotalBytesOnWire.description: The total number of bytes transmitted on wire, including all bytes from collided attempts.

alcetherStatsTxLenChkErrPkts.name: alcetherStatsTxLenChkErrPkts
alcetherStatsTxLenChkErrPkts.description: The total number of transmitted frames for which the frame length field value in the Type/Length field does not match the actual data bytes length and is NOT a Type field.

alcetherStatsTxExcDeferPkts.name: alcetherStatsTxExcDeferPkts
alcetherStatsTxExcDeferPkts.description: The total number of frames that were deferred in excess of 6071 nibble-times in 100 Mbps, 24287 bit-times in 10 Mbps mode. These frames are dropped.(This stat is only in case of Half duplex and excessive defer bit reset).

esmHybridConfTable.name: esmHybridConfTable
esmHybridConfTable.description: A list of inactive hybrid port instances.

esmHybridPortCfgSpeed.name: esmHybridPortCfgSpeed
esmHybridPortCfgSpeed.description: The configured port line speed of this ESM port.

esmHybridPortCfgDuplexMode.name: esmHybridPortCfgDuplexMode
esmHybridPortCfgDuplexMode.description: The configured port duplex mode of this ESM port. Note: GigaEthernet support only full-duplex.

esmHybridPortCfgAutoNegotiation.name: esmHybridPortCfgAutoNegotiation
esmHybridPortCfgAutoNegotiation.description: Allow the user to enable or disable the port auto negotiation.

esmHybridPortCfgCrossover.name: esmHybridPortCfgCrossover
esmHybridPortCfgCrossover.description: Allow the user to configure port crossover.

esmHybridPortCfgFlow.name: esmHybridPortCfgFlow
esmHybridPortCfgFlow.description: This object is used for flow control of hybrid ports. It is similar to the dot3PauseAdminMode object in dot3PauseTable. It is used to configure pause for fiber media.

esmHybridPortCfgInactiveType.name: esmHybridPortCfgInactiveType
esmHybridPortCfgInactiveType.description: This object is only applicable to hybrid ports . It indicates the configured inactive media type.

ddmConfig.name: ddmConfig
ddmConfig.description: This object enables/disables DDM software feature in the system.

ddmTrapConfig.name: ddmTrapConfig
ddmTrapConfig.description: This objects enables/disables traps for DDM warning/alarm threshold violations.

ddmNotificationType.name: ddmNotificationType
ddmNotificationType.description: This object defines the trap type for monitored DDM parameters.

ddmInfoTable.name: ddmInfoTable
ddmInfoTable.description: The ddmInfoTable has an entry for each SFP/XFP in the system that supports Digital Diagnostic Monitoring (DDM). The table is indexed by ifIndex. Each row in this table is dynamically added and removed internally by the system based on the presence or absence of DDM capable SFP/XFP components.

ddmInfoEntry.name: ddmInfoEntry
ddmInfoEntry.description: Each row represents a particular SFP/XFP that supports Digital Diagnostic Monitoring. Entries are created and deleted internally by the system.

ddmTemperature.name: ddmTemperature
ddmTemperature.description: The value of ddmTemperature indicates the current temperature of the SFP/XFP in 1000s of degrees Celsius. A value of -200000 indicates this object is not applicable.

ddmTempLowWarning.name: ddmTempLowWarning
ddmTempLowWarning.description: The value of ddmTempLowWarning indicates the temperature of the SFP/XFP in 1000s of degrees Celsius that triggers a low-warning. A value of -200000 indicates this object is not applicable.

ddmTempLowAlarm.name: ddmTempLowAlarm
ddmTempLowAlarm.description: The value of ddmTempLowAlarm indicates the temperature of the SFP/XFP in 1000s of degrees Celsius that triggers a low-alarm. A value of -200000 indicates this object is not applicable.

ddmTempHiWarning.name: ddmTempHiWarning
ddmTempHiWarning.description: The value of ddmTempHiWarning indicates the temperature of the SFP/XFP in 1000s of degrees Celsius that triggers a hi-warning. A value of -200000 indicates this object is not applicable.

ddmTempHiAlarm.name: ddmTempHiAlarm
ddmTempHiAlarm.description: The value of ddmTempHiAlarm indicates the temperature of the SFP/XFP in 1000s of degrees Celsius that triggers a hi-alarm. A value of -200000 indicates this object is not applicable.

ddmSupplyVoltage.name: ddmSupplyVoltage
ddmSupplyVoltage.description: The value of ddmSupplyVoltage indicates the current supply voltage of the SFP/XFP in 1000s of Volts (V). A value of -200000 indicates this object is not applicable.

ddmSupplyVoltageLowWarning.name: ddmSupplyVoltageLowWarning
ddmSupplyVoltageLowWarning.description: The value of ddmSupplyVoltageLowWarning indicates the supply voltage of the SFP/XFP in 1000s of Volts (V) that triggers a low-warning. A value of -200000 indicates this object is not applicable.

ddmSupplyVoltageLowAlarm.name: ddmSupplyVoltageLowAlarm
ddmSupplyVoltageLowAlarm.description: The value of ddmSupplyVoltageLowAlarm indicates the supply voltage of the SFP/XFP in 1000s of Volts (V) that triggers a low-alarm. A value of -200000 indicates this object is not applicable.

ddmPortInfoTable.name: ddmPortInfoTable
ddmPortInfoTable.description: The ddmPortInfoTable has an entry for each SFP/XFP in the system that supports Digital Diagnostic Monitoring (DDM). The table is indexed by ifIndex and port channel. Each row in this table is dynamically added and removed internally by the system based on the presence or absence of DDM capable SFP/XFP components.

ddmPortInfoEntry.name: ddmPortInfoEntry
ddmPortInfoEntry.description: Each row represents a particular SFP/XFP that supports Digital Diagnostic Monitoring. Entries are created and deleted internally by the system.

ddmPortChannel.name: ddmPortChannel
ddmPortChannel.description: The channel number of the data that is being read. In the case of a QSFP there will be 4 10 gigabyte channels, for SFP/XFP there will only be one.

ddmPortTemperature.name: ddmPortTemperature
ddmPortTemperature.description: The value of ddmTemperature indicates the current temperature of the SFP/XFP in 1000s of degrees Celsius. A value of -200000 indicates this object is not applicable.

alcfcStatsTable.name: alcfcStatsTable
alcfcStatsTable.description: A list of Fiber Channel statistics entries.

alcfcStatsEntry.name: alcfcStatsEntry
alcfcStatsEntry.description: A collection of statistics kept for a particular Fiber Channel interface. As an example, an instance of the fcStatsPkts object might be named alcfcStatsPkts.1

alcfcClearStats.name: alcfcClearStats
alcfcClearStats.description: Used to Clear all Statistics counters. By default, this object contains zero value.

alcfcLastClearStats.name: alcfcLastClearStats
alcfcLastClearStats.description: The value of SysUpTime at the time of all the statistics counters are cleared. By default, this object contains a zero value.

alcfcStatsRxUndersizePkts.name: alcfcStatsRxUndersizePkts
alcfcStatsRxUndersizePkts.description: The total number of packets received that were less than 36 octets long (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and were otherwise well formed.

alcfcStatsTxBBCreditZeros.name: alcfcStatsTxBBCreditZeros
alcfcStatsTxBBCreditZeros.description: The number of transitions in/out of the buffer-to-buffer credit zero state.

alcfcStatsRxBBCreditZeros.name: alcfcStatsRxBBCreditZeros
alcfcStatsRxBBCreditZeros.description: The number of times RX BBCredit drops to zero.

alcfcStatsLossofSynchs.name: alcfcStatsLossofSynchs
alcfcStatsLossofSynchs.description: The number of loss of word-sync detected.

alcfcStatsLossofSignals.name: alcfcStatsLossofSignals
alcfcStatsLossofSignals.description: The number of loss of signals detected.

alcfcStatsPrimSeqProtocolErrors.name: alcfcStatsPrimSeqProtocolErrors
alcfcStatsPrimSeqProtocolErrors.description: The number of primitive sequence protocol errors detected.

alcfcStatsInvalidTxWords.name: alcfcStatsInvalidTxWords
alcfcStatsInvalidTxWords.description: The number of invalid transmission words. This includes invalid ordered sets and invalid data words.

alcfcStatsInvalidCRCs.name: alcfcStatsInvalidCRCs
alcfcStatsInvalidCRCs.description: The number of frames received with an invalid CRC.

alcfcStatsInvalidOrderedSets.name: alcfcStatsInvalidOrderedSets
alcfcStatsInvalidOrderedSets.description: The number of invalid ordered sets received at this port.

alcfcStatsFrameTooLongs.name: alcfcStatsFrameTooLongs
alcfcStatsFrameTooLongs.description: The number of frames received at this port for which the frame length was greater than what was agreed to in FLOGI/PLOGI.

alcfcStatsDelimiterErrors.name: alcfcStatsDelimiterErrors
alcfcStatsDelimiterErrors.description: The number of invalid delimiters received

alcfcStatsEncodingDisparityErrors.name: alcfcStatsEncodingDisparityErrors
alcfcStatsEncodingDisparityErrors.description: The number of detected running disparity at 10b/8b level.

alcfcStatsOtherErrors.name: alcfcStatsOtherErrors
alcfcStatsOtherErrors.description: The number of errors detected but not counted by any other error counter. This only includes RX frames drops due to zero RX BBCredits

esmDrvTrapDropsLink.name: esmDrvTrapDropsLink
esmDrvTrapDropsLink.description: When the Ethernet code drops the link because of excessive errors, a Trap is sent.

ddmTemperatureThresholdViolated.name: ddmTemperatureThresholdViolated
ddmTemperatureThresholdViolated.description: This object notifies management station if an SFP/XFP/SFP+ temperature has crossed any threshold or reverted from previous threshold violation for a port represented by ifIndex. It also provides the current realtime value of SFP/XFP/SFP+ temperature.

ddmVoltageThresholdViolated.name: ddmVoltageThresholdViolated
ddmVoltageThresholdViolated.description: This object notifies management station if an SFP/XFP/SFP+ supply voltage has crossed any threshold or reverted from previous threshold violation for a port represented by ifIndex. It also provides the current realtime value of SFP/XFP/SFP+ supply voltage.

ddmCurrentThresholdViolated.name: ddmCurrentThresholdViolated
ddmCurrentThresholdViolated.description: This object notifies management station if an SFP/XFP/SFP+ Tx bias current has crossed any threshold or reverted from previous threshold violation for a port represented by ifIndex. It also provides the current realtime value of SFP/XFP/SFP+ Tx bias current.

ddmTxPowerThresholdViolated.name: ddmTxPowerThresholdViolated
ddmTxPowerThresholdViolated.description: This object notifies management station if an SFP/XFP/SFP+ Tx output power has crossed any threshold or reverted from previous threshold violation for a port represented by ifIndex. It also provides the current realtime value of SFP/XFP/SFP+ Tx output power.

ddmRxPowerThresholdViolated.name: ddmRxPowerThresholdViolated
ddmRxPowerThresholdViolated.description: This object notifies management station if an SFP/XFP/SFP+ Rx optical power has crossed any threshold or reverted from previous threshold violation for a port represented by ifIndex. It also provides the current realtime value of SFP/XFP/SFP+ Rx optical power.

portViolationTable.name: portViolationTable
portViolationTable.description: This table contains the port Violations per port.

portViolationEntry.name: portViolationEntry
portViolationEntry.description: Port Violation Entry. The entries in this table are indexed by 3 units, 1. ifIndex of the port for which the violation is set 2. source of the violation, the feature or module 3. reason for the violation (sub reason under each source).

portViolationIfIndex.name: portViolationIfIndex
portViolationIfIndex.description: The IfIndex of the port that has a violation.

portViolationSource.name: portViolationSource
portViolationSource.description: Indicates the source of the port violation. The source is the feature or module that has caused the violation. The list is given below 1. Initiated by Source Learning 2. Initiated by QOS Policy 3. Initiated by Net Sec 4. Initiated by UDLD 5. Initiated by NI supervison (Fabric Stability). When there is no value the value of this will be 0

portViolationReason.name: portViolationReason
portViolationReason.description: The Reason for the port violation. This will be application specific. The Reason indicate the violation for the 1st Violation that happened on this port.

portViolationAction.name: portViolationAction
portViolationAction.description: The action determines on violation, what action will taken. Either the port would be shutdown or Admin Down or wait for the timer to expire and the timerAction will determine what needs to be done.

portViolationTimer.name: portViolationTimer
portViolationTimer.description: If any timer is associated with the violation This is Zero if no timer is associated.

portViolationTimerAction.name: portViolationTimerAction
portViolationTimerAction.description: The Timer related action. If set to portDownAfterTimer, no operation will be performed on the port and the port will be shutdown after timer expiry. If set to portUpAfterTimer the port will be shutdown immediately and after the timer expiry the port will brought up..

portViolationClearPort.name: portViolationClearPort
portViolationClearPort.description: When this MIB object is set all violation on the given port will be cleared. The Indices portViolationSource and portViolationReason should be set to 0

alaLinkMonConfigTable.name: alaLinkMonConfigTable
alaLinkMonConfigTable.description: A list of Link Monitoring Configuration Parameters

alaLinkMonConfigEntry.name: alaLinkMonConfigEntry
alaLinkMonConfigEntry.description: A collection of Link Monitoring configurations kept for a particular Ethernet interface.

alaLinkMonStatus.name: alaLinkMonStatus
alaLinkMonStatus.description: Allows the user to enable or disable Link Monitoring on the port.

alaLinkMonTimeWindow.name: alaLinkMonTimeWindow
alaLinkMonTimeWindow.description: Indicates the number of seconds the Link will be monitored for a port.

alaLinkMonLinkFlapThreshold.name: alaLinkMonLinkFlapThreshold
alaLinkMonLinkFlapThreshold.description: Indicaes the number of link flaps allowed for the specified port during the time window before the port is shutdown.

alaLinkMonLinkErrorThreshold.name: alaLinkMonLinkErrorThreshold
alaLinkMonLinkErrorThreshold.description: Indicates the number of link errors allowed on Rx for the specified port during the time window before the port is shutdown. The errors are the MAC errors that include CRC, lost frames, error frames, alignment frames.

alaLinkMonWaitToRestoreTimer.name: alaLinkMonWaitToRestoreTimer
alaLinkMonWaitToRestoreTimer.description: Indicates the number of seconds after which the link up event is notified to other applications. The timer is started whenever a Link Up is detected on a port being monitored.

alaLinkMonWaitToShutdownTimer.name: alaLinkMonWaitToShutdownTimer
alaLinkMonWaitToShutdownTimer.description: Indicates the number of milli seconds after which the link down event is notified to other applications. The timer is started whenever a Link down is detected on a port being monitored.

alaLinkMonStatsTable.name: alaLinkMonStatsTable
alaLinkMonStatsTable.description: A list of Link Monitoring Statistics

alaLinkMonStatsEntry.name: alaLinkMonStatsEntry
alaLinkMonStatsEntry.description: A collection of Link Monitoring statistics for a particular Ethernet interface.

alaLinkMonStatsClearStats.name: alaLinkMonStatsClearStats
alaLinkMonStatsClearStats.description: Used to Clear all Statistics counters. The value reset (1) indicates that Link Monitoring shuold all statistic counters related to the particular port. By default, this object contains zero value.

alaLinkMonStatsPortState.name: alaLinkMonStatsPortState
alaLinkMonStatsPortState.description: Indicates the status of the port. up(1) means the port is physically up, down(2) means the port is physically down, shutdown(3) means the interface is shutdown because of excessive link flaps or link errors.

alaLinkMonStatsCurrentLinkFlaps.name: alaLinkMonStatsCurrentLinkFlaps
alaLinkMonStatsCurrentLinkFlaps.description: Indicates the number of Link flaps in the current time window.

alaLinkMonStatsCurrentErrorFrames.name: alaLinkMonStatsCurrentErrorFrames
alaLinkMonStatsCurrentErrorFrames.description: Indicates the number of error frames in the current time window.

alaLinkMonStatsCurrentCRCErrors.name: alaLinkMonStatsCurrentCRCErrors
alaLinkMonStatsCurrentCRCErrors.description: Indicates the number of CRC errors in the current time window.

alaLinkMonStatsCurrentLostFrames.name: alaLinkMonStatsCurrentLostFrames
alaLinkMonStatsCurrentLostFrames.description: Indicates the number of Rx Lost frames in the current time window.

alaLinkMonStatsCurrentAlignErrors.name: alaLinkMonStatsCurrentAlignErrors
alaLinkMonStatsCurrentAlignErrors.description: Indicates the number of Rx alignment frames in the current time window.

alaLinkMonStatsCurrentLinkErrors.name: alaLinkMonStatsCurrentLinkErrors
alaLinkMonStatsCurrentLinkErrors.description: Indicates the sum of all the MAC Errors within the current time window. i.e., the sum of alaLinkMonStatsCurrentErrorFrames, alaLinkMonStatsCurrentCRCErrors, alaLinkMonCurrentLosFrames, alaLinkMonStatsCurrentAlignErrors.

alaLinkMonStatsTotalLinkFlaps.name: alaLinkMonStatsTotalLinkFlaps
alaLinkMonStatsTotalLinkFlaps.description: Indicates the total number of link flaps across all the time windows.

alaLinkMonStatsTotalLinkErrors.name: alaLinkMonStatsTotalLinkErrors
alaLinkMonStatsTotalLinkErrors.description: Indicates the total number of link errors across all the time windows.

alaLFPGroupTable.name: alaLFPGroupTable
alaLFPGroupTable.description: A list of Link Fault Propagation Grooups and their status

alaLFPGroupEntry.name: alaLFPGroupEntry
alaLFPGroupEntry.description: The list of Link Fault Propagation group id and status for each group

alaLFPGroupId.name: alaLFPGroupId
alaLFPGroupId.description: Indicates the unique group id for Link Fault Propagation (LFP).

alaLFPGroupAdminStatus.name: alaLFPGroupAdminStatus
alaLFPGroupAdminStatus.description: Indicates the admin status of the group. disable(2) means link fault propagation, is disbaled. enable(1) means link fault propagation is enabled

alaLFPGroupOperStatus.name: alaLFPGroupOperStatus
alaLFPGroupOperStatus.description: Indicates the operational status of the group. down(2) means all the source ports are down, up(1) means atleast one source port in the group is up.

alaLFPGroupWaitToShutdown.name: alaLFPGroupWaitToShutdown
alaLFPGroupWaitToShutdown.description: 0 - Disable wait to shutdown timer 5 - 300 - after expiry of this timer all destination ports will be shutdown

alaLFPGroupRowStatus.name: alaLFPGroupRowStatus
alaLFPGroupRowStatus.description: Row Status for initiating a MIB retrieval request.

alaLFPConfigTable.name: alaLFPConfigTable
alaLFPConfigTable.description: A list of Link Fault Propagation port and port type of each LFP group

alaLFPConfigEntry.name: alaLFPConfigEntry
alaLFPConfigEntry.description: A list of Link Fault Propagation port and port type of each LFP group

alaLFPConfigPort.name: alaLFPConfigPort
alaLFPConfigPort.description: Indicates ifindex of source/destination port for a LFP Group.

alaLFPConfigPortType.name: alaLFPConfigPortType
alaLFPConfigPortType.description: Indicates the type of port, (1) means the port is destination port and (2) means the port is a destination port for a LFP Group.

alaLFPConfigRowStatus.name: alaLFPConfigRowStatus
alaLFPConfigRowStatus.description: Row Status for initiating a MIB retrieval request.

portViolationTrap.name: portViolationTrap
portViolationTrap.description: A Trap will be generated when a port violation occurs. The port violation trap will indicate the source of the violation and the reason for the violation.

portViolationNotificationTrap.name: portViolationNotificationTrap
portViolationNotificationTrap.description: A Trap will be generated when a port violation is cleared.

esmConfPortCompliance.name: esmConfPortCompliance
esmConfPortCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the configuration of Ethernet ports.

alcEtherStatsCompliance.name: alcEtherStatsCompliance
alcEtherStatsCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the Statistics of the Ethernet ports.

esmConfMIBGroup.name: esmConfMIBGroup
esmConfMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects to support the management of global configuration parameters of the Ethernet ports.

esmDetectedConfMIBGroup.name: esmDetectedConfMIBGroup
esmDetectedConfMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects to support the Detected configuration parameters of the Ethernet ports.

alcEtherStatsMIBGroup.name: alcEtherStatsMIBGroup
alcEtherStatsMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects to provide all the statistics related to the Ethernet and GigaEthernert ports.

ddmInfoGroup.name: ddmInfoGroup
ddmInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects to provide digital diagnostics information related to SFPs, XFPs, and SFP+s.

ddmConfigGroup.name: ddmConfigGroup
ddmConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects to allow configuration of DDM and DDM traps.

ddmNotificationsGroup.name: ddmNotificationsGroup
ddmNotificationsGroup.description: A collection of notifications used to indicate DDM threshold violations.

esmHybridConfEntryGroup.name: esmHybridConfEntryGroup
esmHybridConfEntryGroup.description: A list of inactive hybrid port instances.

esmConfEntryGroup.name: esmConfEntryGroup
esmConfEntryGroup.description: A list of ESM Physical Port instances.

portViolationEntryGroup.name: portViolationEntryGroup
portViolationEntryGroup.description: This table contains the port Violations per port.

ddmPortInfoGroup.name: ddmPortInfoGroup
ddmPortInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects to provide digital diagnostics information related to SFPs, XFPs, and SFP+s.

alaLinkMonConfigMIBGroup.name: alaLinkMonConfigMIBGroup
alaLinkMonConfigMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects to support the Link Monitoring Configurations on the ports.

alaLinkMonStatsMIBGroup.name: alaLinkMonStatsMIBGroup
